Good catch on angle indicators. The Arc radius is 20px (line 153), and labels can extend another ~15px (line 158). So we need to expand bounding box by ~35px in all directions where angles are shown.

**Enhanced Bounding Box Calculation:**
```javascript
function getTriangleBoundsWithAnnotations(vertices, sides, angles) {
  let bounds = getTriangleBounds(vertices);

  // Account for side labels (perpendicular offset ~15px + text width ~20px)
  bounds.minX -= 35;
  bounds.maxX += 35;
  bounds.minY -= 35;
  bounds.maxY += 35;

  // Account for angle indicators (arc radius 20 + label 15)
  if (angles && angles.some(a => a.show)) {
    bounds.minX -= 35;
    bounds.maxX += 35;
    bounds.minY -= 35;
    bounds.maxY += 35;
  }

  return bounds;
}
```

This ensures the full rendered triangle (with all labels and arcs) fits within bounds.
